org.jibble.pircbot
Class User

java.lang.Object
  org.jibble.pircbot.User
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class User
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class is used to represent a user on an IRC server. Instances of this class are returned by the getUser and getUsers methods in the PircBot class.

Note that this class no longer implements the Comparable interface for Java 1.1 compatibility reasons.

public java.lang.String getPrefix()
Returns the prefix of the user. If the User object has been obtained from a list of users in a channel, then this will reflect the user's status in that channel.

hasPrefix

public boolean hasPrefix(java.lang.String prefix)
Returns whether or not the user represented by this object has the given prefix. If the User object has been obtained from a list of users in a channel, then this will reflect the user's status in that channel. This is useful for checking non-standard prefixes that may exist on different networks (IRCd's).

Parameters:
prefix - the prefix to check for
Returns:
true if the user has the given prefix.
